      <SubComponents>
        <Component class="javax.swing.JTextArea" name="jTextArea1">
          <Properties>
            <Property name="editable" type="boolean" value="false"/>
            <Property name="columns" type="int" value="20"/>
            <Property name="lineWrap" type="boolean" value="true"/>
            <Property name="rows" type="int" value="5"/>
            <Property name="text" type="java.lang.String" value="Visit the project page for a brief introduction: https://hartrusion.com/en/rbmk-simulator/&#xa;&#xa;The simulation starts with the Blowdown/Cooldown system in place to remove heat from the core, no MCP is active. Close the bypass, use MCP for recirculation and modify the paths of the feedwater to make sure the reheater is in use, this reduces heat removal from the core.&#xa;&#xa;Certain alarms need to be cleared to allow resetting the RPS. To start the nuclear chain reaction, pull out enough manual rods (fully pull them out one by one, do not move all at once!) to get to a reactivity where the auto rods can be used to control the reactivity around 0.&#xa;&#xa;Use a neutron flux of about 4 % and until that, remove the heat using the auxiliary condensers. Use the startup ejectors to evacuate the condensers.&#xa;&#xa;When condensation is available, start warming up the turbine using the startup valves. You need about 350 MWth to sync to the grid."/>
            <Property name="wrapStyleWord" type="boolean" value="true"/>
          </Properties>
        </Component>
      </SubComponents>
    </Container>
  </SubComponents>
